    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="336"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3831/64a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-29T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 29, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Please inform Haitian Government that the Department intends to give public
                    notice shortly of this Government’s intention to negotiate a Reciprocal Foreign
                    Trade Agreement with the Government of Haiti.<note n="37" xml:id="d336fn37">For
                        text of public notice and statistics on trade between the United States and
                        Haiti, issued by the Department of State on August 31, 1934, see Department
                        of State, <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, September 1, 1934, pp.
                        144–150.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
